e in the Middle Ages by various rulers in south-west Wales, including  Rhys ap Tewdur  (  d. 1093 ) and  Rhys ap Gruffudd  (  1132–97 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Reece","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of Rhys . The name is now in widespread and frequent use outside Wales, in many cases representing a transferred use of the surname so spelled, which is derived from the given name."]},{"name":"Rees","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of Welsh Rhys, in some cases representing a transferred use of the surname so spelled, which is derived from the Welsh given name."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Rhys ap Hywel was born about 1280, in Gladestry, Radnorshire, Wales. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Rhys ap Hywel."},"et":{"about 1280–":"umbes 1280–Surnud","1274–1328":"1274–1328","1300–1348":"1300–1348","1302–Male":"1302–Surnud","1280–Female":"1280–Surnud","1348":"1348","about 1280":"umbes 1280","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","about 1302":"umbes 1302","1274":"1274","1280":"1280","1328":"1328","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","Gladestry, Radnorshire, Wales":"Gladestry, Radnorshire, Wales","Talgarth, Breconshire, Wales":"Talgarth, Breconshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1280–":"noin 1280–Kuollut","1274–1328":"1274–1328","1300–1348":"1300–1348","1302–Male":"1302–Kuollut","1280–Female":"1280–Kuollut","1348":"1348","about 1280":"noin 1280","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","about 1302":"noin 1302","1274":"1274","1280":"1280","1328":"1328","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gladestry, Radnorshire, Wales":"Gladestry, Radnorshire, Wales","Talgarth, Breconshire, Wales":"Talgarth, Breconshire, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1280–":"environ 1280–Décédée","1274–1328":"1274–1328","1300–1348":"1300–1348","1302–Male":"1302–Décédé","1280–Female":"1280–Décédée","1348":"1348","about 1280":"environ 1280","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","about 1302":"environ 1302","1274":"1274","1280":"1280","1328":"1328","Wales, United Kingdom":"Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Gladestry, Radnorshire, 